  "bib_entries": {
    "28340840": {
      "title": "Theory and experiments on elastic band gaps",
      "abstract": "We study elastic band gaps in nonhomogeneous periodic finite media. The finite-difference timedomain method is used for the first time in the field of elastic band-gap materials. It is used to interpret experimental data for two-dimensional systems consisting of cylinders of fluids (Hg, air, and oil) inserted periodically in a finite slab of aluminum host. The method provides good convergence, can be applied to realistic finite composite slabs, even to composites with a huge contrast in the elastic parameters of their components, and describes well the experiments."
